    patientExplanation: 'Endocarditis is a serious infection of the heart valves. Bacteria in the bloodstream attach to a heart valve and form a growth called a vegetation. This can damage the valve, cause it to leak, and send infected pieces to other organs like the brain or kidneys. It requires weeks of strong IV antibiotics. Some patients need surgery to replace the infected valve. Preventing it starts with good dental hygiene and, for some high-risk patients, antibiotics before dental procedures.',
