    clinicalFeatures: ['Dyspnea on exertion', 'Exercise intolerance', 'Peripheral edema, ascites', 'Elevated JVP with prominent y descent (rapid early filling then abrupt halt)', 'Kussmaul sign may be present', 'S3 or S4 gallop', 'Hepatomegaly', 'Low voltage on ECG despite thick walls (amyloidosis - pseudohypertrophy)', 'Atrial fibrillation'],
