    pathophysiology: 'Viral infection (coxsackievirus B, adenovirus, parvovirus B19, SARS-CoV-2, HHV-6) causes direct myocyte injury and immune-mediated damage. Phase 1: viral entry and myocyte necrosis. Phase 2: adaptive immune response with T-cell and antibody-mediated injury. Phase 3: recovery or progression to chronic dilated cardiomyopathy. Non-infectious causes include autoimmune (giant cell myocarditis, eosinophilic), drugs (immune checkpoint inhibitors, cocaine), and toxins.',
