    treatment: ['Supportive care: rest, avoid exercise for 3-6 months', 'Standard heart failure therapy if reduced EF (ACEi, beta-blocker, diuretics)', 'Hemodynamic support for fulminant: inotropes, mechanical circulatory support (Impella, ECMO)', 'Immunosuppression for giant cell myocarditis (steroids + cyclosporine/azathioprine)', 'Avoid NSAIDs (may worsen myocardial inflammation in animal models)', 'ICD if persistent EF <=35% after 3-6 months of optimal therapy (avoid early implant as many recover)', 'Wearable defibrillator (LifeVest) as bridge during recovery period'],
