    pathophysiology: 'Inflammation of the pericardial layers (visceral and parietal) from infectious (viral most common: coxsackievirus, echovirus, adenovirus), autoimmune (SLE, RA), post-cardiac injury (Dressler syndrome post-MI, post-pericardiotomy), metabolic (uremia), neoplastic, or idiopathic causes. Inflammation produces serous, fibrinous, or purulent fluid. Pericardial effusion may accumulate. Recurrence occurs in 15-30% of cases.',
