    treatment: ['NSAIDs (ibuprofen 600mg TID or aspirin 750-1000mg TID) for 1-2 weeks with taper', 'Colchicine 0.5mg BID for 3 months (reduces recurrence by 50%)', 'Avoid anticoagulants if possible (hemorrhagic pericarditis risk)', 'Activity restriction until symptoms resolve and CRP normalizes', 'Athletes: 3 months rest minimum', 'Corticosteroids only as last resort (increase recurrence risk) or for autoimmune/uremic', 'Pericardiectomy for refractory recurrent pericarditis', 'Treat underlying cause (dialysis for uremic, antibiotics for purulent)'],
