    treatment: ['Emergent pericardiocentesis (needle drainage of pericardial fluid, usually echo-guided)', 'IV fluid bolus (increase preload to maintain cardiac output as bridge)', 'Avoid diuretics, vasodilators, and positive pressure ventilation (all decrease preload, worsen tamponade)', 'Pericardial drain placement after pericardiocentesis', 'Surgical pericardial window for recurrent effusions', 'Definitive treatment of underlying cause (malignancy, uremia, infection, autoimmune)', 'Emergent thoracotomy for traumatic tamponade'],
