    description: 'Atherosclerotic narrowing of the coronary arteries reducing myocardial blood supply, the leading cause of death worldwide.',
    pathophysiology: 'Endothelial injury from hypertension, smoking, dyslipidemia, and diabetes initiates atherosclerosis. LDL cholesterol deposits in the arterial wall, oxidizes, and triggers macrophage infiltration forming foam cells. A fibrous cap forms over the lipid-rich core creating a plaque. Stable plaques cause fixed obstruction (stable angina when >70% stenosis). Vulnerable plaques with thin caps can rupture, exposing thrombogenic core to blood, triggering acute thrombosis (ACS). Collateral circulation may develop in chronic disease.',
    clinicalFeatures: ['Stable angina: predictable exertional chest pressure/tightness, relieved by rest or nitroglycerin', 'Radiation to left arm, jaw, neck, or back', 'Associated dyspnea, diaphoresis, nausea', 'Levine sign (clenched fist over sternum)', 'Atypical presentations more common in women, elderly, diabetics (dyspnea, fatigue, nausea)', 'May be asymptomatic (silent ischemia, especially in diabetics)'],
    diagnostics: ['Exercise stress ECG (standard first-line if can exercise and interpretable ECG)', 'Stress imaging (nuclear, echo, or CMR) if unable to exercise or baseline ECG abnormalities', 'Coronary CT angiography for intermediate pretest probability', 'Coronary calcium score for risk stratification in asymptomatic patients', 'Invasive coronary angiography (gold standard) for high-risk findings or planned intervention', 'Lipid panel, HbA1c, BMP, high-sensitivity CRP'],
    treatment: ['Lifestyle: Mediterranean diet, exercise 150 min/week, smoking cessation, weight management', 'Antiplatelet: aspirin 81mg daily', 'Statin therapy (high-intensity: atorvastatin 40-80mg or rosuvastatin 20-40mg)', 'Blood pressure control (<130/80)', 'Glycemic control if diabetic', 'Antianginal: beta-blockers, CCBs, long-acting nitrates, ranolazine', 'PCI with stenting for significant stenosis with symptoms or ischemia', 'CABG for left main disease, 3-vessel disease with reduced EF, or complex anatomy'],
