    patientExplanation: 'Aortic dissection is a tear in the wall of the aorta, your body largest artery. Blood forces its way between the layers of the artery wall, which can block blood flow to vital organs and even rupture. It causes sudden, severe chest or back pain often described as tearing or ripping. This is a life-threatening emergency. If the tear involves the part of the aorta near the heart, emergency surgery is needed. Blood pressure must be lowered quickly to prevent the tear from spreading.',
    emergencySigns: ['This IS a life-threatening emergency - call 911 immediately', 'Sudden severe tearing chest/back pain', 'Unequal blood pressures or pulses between arms', 'Signs of malperfusion (stroke, limb ischemia, abdominal pain)', 'Hypotension suggesting rupture or tamponade'],
