    clinicalFeatures: ['Unilateral leg swelling (most specific)', 'Pain and tenderness along deep veins', 'Warmth and erythema', 'Pitting edema', 'Homan sign (calf pain with dorsiflexion - poor sensitivity/specificity)', 'Palpable cord', 'Dilated superficial veins', 'May be asymptomatic (incidental finding)', 'Upper extremity DVT: arm swelling (Paget-Schroetter in young athletes, catheter-associated)'],
    diagnostics: ['Wells score for pretest probability', 'D-dimer to rule out in low probability (negative D-dimer + low Wells = DVT excluded)', 'Compression ultrasonography (first-line imaging): non-compressible vein = DVT', 'Whole-leg ultrasound vs proximal-only (varies by institution)', 'CT venography or MR venography for iliac vein or abdominal DVT', 'Thrombophilia workup: consider if unprovoked, recurrent, unusual site, or strong family history (defer testing until off anticoagulation)'],
