    clinicalFeatures: ['Intermittent claudication (calf, thigh, or buttock pain with walking, relieved by rest)', 'Reproducible walking distance', 'Critical limb ischemia: rest pain (especially at night, hanging leg off bed provides relief), non-healing ulcers, gangrene', 'Diminished or absent peripheral pulses', 'Cool extremities, pallor on elevation, dependent rubor', 'Hair loss, shiny skin, thickened nails', 'Bruits over narrowed arteries', 'Leriche syndrome: bilateral buttock claudication, impotence, absent femoral pulses (aortoiliac disease)'],
    diagnostics: ['Ankle-brachial index (ABI): <0.9 diagnostic of PAD, <0.4 severe/CLI', 'ABI >1.4: non-compressible calcified vessels (diabetes, renal failure) - use toe pressures', 'Segmental pressures and pulse volume recordings', 'Duplex ultrasonography for anatomic localization', 'CT or MR angiography for intervention planning', 'Conventional angiography if intervention planned', 'Assess for coexistent CAD and cerebrovascular disease'],
    treatment: ['Supervised exercise therapy (walking program, 30-45 min, 3x/week for 12 weeks - first-line for claudication)', 'Smoking cessation (critical)', 'Antiplatelet therapy (aspirin or clopidogrel)', 'Statin therapy (cardiovascular risk reduction)', 'Blood pressure and diabetes control', 'Cilostazol for claudication symptoms (avoid in HF)', 'Revascularization for lifestyle-limiting claudication refractory to exercise therapy', 'Critical limb ischemia: urgent revascularization (endovascular or surgical bypass)', 'Amputation as last resort for non-salvageable tissue'],
