    pathophysiology: 'Myocardial injury (ischemic, toxic, genetic, infectious) reduces contractile function. Compensatory mechanisms activate: Frank-Starling (increased preload), sympathetic nervous system (increased HR/contractility), RAAS (sodium/water retention, vasoconstriction), natriuretic peptides. Initially adaptive, chronic neurohormonal activation causes progressive ventricular remodeling (dilation, spherical shape change, fibrosis), functional MR, and further systolic decline. This vicious cycle drives disease progression.',
