    diagnostics: ['Echocardiography: LVEF <=40%, LV dilation, wall motion abnormalities, valvular assessment', 'BNP >100 pg/mL or NT-proBNP >300 pg/mL supports diagnosis', 'CXR: cardiomegaly, cephalization of pulmonary vessels, pleural effusions, Kerley B lines', 'ECG: may show LVH, LBBB, Q waves, arrhythmias', 'Labs: BMP (renal function, electrolytes), CBC, TSH, iron studies, LFTs', 'Coronary assessment to exclude ischemic etiology', 'Cardiac MRI for etiology and tissue characterization'],
    treatment: ['Quadruple therapy (4 pillars): ARNI (sacubitril/valsartan) or ACEi/ARB + evidence-based beta-blocker (carvedilol, metoprolol succinate, bisoprolol) + MRA (spironolactone or eplerenone) + SGLT2i (dapagliflozin or empagliflozin)', 'Diuretics for congestion (loop diuretics: furosemide, bumetanide, torsemide)', 'Hydralazine/isosorbide dinitrate (especially African Americans, or ACEi/ARB-intolerant)', 'ICD if EF <=35% despite 3 months GDMT (primary prevention SCD)', 'CRT if LBBB with QRS >=150ms and EF <=35%', 'Ivabradine if HR >=70 on maximally tolerated beta-blocker', 'Advanced therapies: LVAD, heart transplant for end-stage (Stage D)', 'Cardiac rehabilitation'],
